- Use functional components and hooks for state management
- Optimize performance with React.memo and useCallback
- Implement proper error handling with Error Boundaries
- Utilize Expo's built-in features for notifications and permissions
- Use Expo Router for file-based navigation
- Implement proper TypeScript types for all components
- Use the shared UI package for consistent styling across platforms
- Follow the Palmera design system tokens for colors and typography
- Implement proper loading states and error handling in mobile components
- Use Expo's secure storage for sensitive data like auth tokens
- Implement proper image optimization with Expo Image
- Use Expo's location services for location-based features
- Implement proper push notification handling with Expo Notifications
- Use Expo's camera and media library for KYC document uploads
- Follow accessibility guidelines for mobile components